reviews.title: It's usable
reviews.review_text: Unlike other reviewers, mine came complete despite being in a destroyed box and delivered to the wrong place that being said the first thing I would do is throw away the couplings as for the bar itself the knurling is pretty much nonexistent and the powder coat isn't much better than spray paint but it seems that the bar would hold the weight that it is rated for

reviews.title: Review of PACKAGING, not the barbell itself.
reviews.review_text: The barbell was shipped with nothing but bubble wrap over the ends, secured with cable ties. The bar was covered with a cardboard tube in the center that only went about two-thirds the length of the bar. The bar's bare metal was exposed and the bubble wrap on the ends was worn through from scraping on the ground during shipping. Hopefully the replacement will be packed better! I'll post a new review of the replacement.

reviews.title: Missing parts
reviews.review_text: The bar is fine. When received, the packaging was just loosely taped on one end, no plastic cap for the tube like the other end. I am missing one collar and both screws for the collars.
I like the weight of the bar and the feel of the bar but the paint does come off... stained my bench first day

reviews.title: Just as described, came on time
reviews.review_text: Just as described, came on time

reviews.title: A little rough but functional.
reviews.review_text: Well it's cheap. I had to take the ends off because they were full of metal chips from the machining process. A simple shake and they fell out so the kid who made it in China is slacking. They spin freely (supposed to) and squeak as they do. Slightly annoying but it works. If you don't want a bar that might squeak then buy one with bearings. Knurling is good.

reviews.title: Brocken part
reviews.review_text: Item came with a broken part I had to return it to get a replacement I guess I will give you a better review once I get it again and start using it.
